    • Field Detail

      • EXPOSURE_FPS_RANGE

        public static final ParameterKey.Key<Scope<Integer>> EXPOSURE_FPS_RANGE
        Indicates the key of a frame rate range that the AE can reach.

        This key can be used to set the frame rate range for image sampling. To set a specific frame rate, ensure that the upper and lower limits of the range are the same. For example, you can use [30,30] to set the sampling frame rate to 30 fps.

        Since:
        3

      • IMAGE_COMPRESSION_QUALITY

        public static final ParameterKey.Key<Byte> IMAGE_COMPRESSION_QUALITY
        Indicates compression quality control.

        Range from 1 to 100, typical value is 90. Larger is higher quality, lower compression.

        Since:
        1
